{"word":"αἴλινος","slug":"αἴλινος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἴλινος</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a plaintive dirge</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; (said to be from <el>αἶ Λίνον</el>, <i>ah me for Linus!</i> <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:Λίνος'><el>Λίνος</el></a> II.)<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <el>αἴλινος, ον</el>, <i>mournful, plaintive</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>αἴλινα</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Moschus'>Mosch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}